                            <comment id="17322613" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2021 04:50:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay sounds like it should have a pluggable idempotent repository (like file component etc) where you can set an upper limit of entries to keep.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OOM will take a very long time as a sha is not a big object.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17322843" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2021 10:46:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like we can use &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public List&amp;lt;RepositoryCommit&amp;gt; getCommits(IRepositoryIdProvider repository,&lt;br/&gt;
			String sha, String path) throws IOException {&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where sha is the last known sha, then the commit service should not start from the beginning for each poll.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
